[33mcommit 0faa1912e04f7372e7244bd1a8877f3f9da80df1[m[33m ([m[1;31morigin/fixNamespaceAdd[m[33m, [m[1;32mfixNamespaceAdd[m[33m)[m
Author: jaellio <jaellio@microsoft.com>
Date:   Thu Dec 2 21:07:17 2021 -0500

    fix(cli): set sidecar injection annotation to disabled
    
    Modifies the patch command on `osm namespace add --disable-sidecar
    -injection` to set the sidecar injection annotation to "disabled"
    instead of null. Patching the annotation key with a null value
    should have removed the annotation if it existed or had no effect
    if the annotation key did not exist. Currently, when the
    sidecar injection annotation does not exist on the namespace, the
    patch mentioned above adds te annotation with a value of an empty
    string. This result is errors in the osm-injector when pods are
    added to the namespace.
    
    This PR also includes a change to notify the user if the namespace
    being added is already monitored by the mesh.
    
    Signed-off-by: jaellio <jaellio@microsoft.com>

[33mcommit 8dccabbf98d4187d7072b2145b1e280d45303f6d[m
Author: Shashank Ram <21697719+shashankram@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Thu Dec 2 22:32:01 2021 +0530

    injector: rename iptables chains for clarity (#4379)
    
    Renames the iptables chains and prefixes the
    custom chains with `OSM_` to indicate these
    chains are owned by OSM.
    
    It renames the custom chains as follows:
    PROXY_INBOUND -> OSM_PROXY_INBOUND
    PROXY_OUTPUT -> OSM_PROXY_OUTBOUND
    PROXY_IN_REDIRECT -> OSM_PROXY_IN_REDIRECT
    PROXY_REDIRECT -> OSM_PROXY_OUT_REDIRECT
    
    Signed-off-by: Shashank Ram <shashr2204@gmail.com>

[33mcommit 6d99e8aad055b4bc336febac56cf83db2e6be591[m
