[33mcommit 65c0c6d0d50c803c8ca73d3c246d6e8545a5ae6f[m
Author: Johnson Shi <Johnson.Shi@microsoft.com>
Date:   Fri Oct 22 15:13:43 2021 -0700

    feat(cli): add uninstall cluster-wide-resources cmd
    
    This adds a command `osm uninstall cluster-wide-resources`,
    which uninstalls cluster-wide resources that may have been
    left over after osm was previously uninstalled
    (through `osm uninstall mesh`, through helm, or through
    uninstallation in a managed environment).
    
    When `osm uninstall mesh` is run, the helm post-delete hook
    is invoked as part of the uninstall process. This deletes:
    (1) osm control plane pods (in the osm namespace)
    (2) osm control plane secrets (in the osm namespace)
    (3) mutating webhook configurations
    (4) validating webhook configurations
    (5) osm control plane mesh config
    
    OSM CRDs and SMI CRDs are not deleted by the helm
    post-delete hook.
    
    Additionally, all of the above are not deleted when osm
    is uninstalled from a cluster in a managed environment,
    as the helm post-delete hook is typically not executed
    in such environments.
    
    This new subcommand ensures that the following are deleted
    from the cluster, whether the cluster is managed or not:
    (1) OSM CRDs
    (2) SMI CRDs
    (3) OSM MutatingWebhookConfigurations
    (4) OSM ValidatingWebhookConfigurations
    (5) OSM Secrets
    
    Resolves #4255.
    
    Signed-off-by: Johnson Shi <Johnson.Shi@microsoft.com>

