[33mcommit ceb6044a59ca522143e3eec65fc4f3f73e3e169c[m
Author: jaellio <jaellio@microsoft.com>
Date:   Tue Oct 12 12:14:30 2021 -0700

    feat(metrics): monitored namespaces prometheus metric
    
    Adds a monitored namespace counter guage. StartNamespaceCounter
    is a goroutine that subscribes to the namespace added and deleted
    events on the KubeEventPubSub. The metric is updated based on
    these events.
    
    The Monitored Namespace Count panel was updated to use the
    MonitoredNamespaceCouter metric. The count is no longer calculated
    by subracting the number of namespace deleted events from the
    number of namespace added events obtained from the
    k8sApiEventCounter. As descibed in #3918, the previous PromQL query
    did not accurately determine the difference between the counter
    vectors. This change removes the reliance on the k8sApiEventCounter
    to determine resource counts.
    
    Removes Number of Pods, and Services in the Mesh panels from the
    Grafana dashboard. Currently, osm Prometheus metrics do not exist
    to accurately determine the number of resources in the mesh.
    Future PRs will add these metrics and add panels to the dashboard.
    
    Addresses #3918
    
    Signed-off-by: jaellio <jaellio@microsoft.com>

[33mcommit a09731eda755aee78a1a5bd5a67e301468423ce6[m
