[33mcommit 99f64e79378a21c8035abdf026882325c7c3c684[m
Author: Shashank Ram <21697719+shashankram@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri Oct 15 10:30:07 2021 -0700

    messaging/proxy: avoid unnecessary proxy broadcasts (#4265)
    
    Avoids unnecessary proxy broadcasts for pod and service
    events.
    
    Pod add/delete events will result in endpoint
    add/delete events for pods backing a service, which
    are already triggering proxy broadcast events. Pod add
    events are also going to trigger XDS gRPC connects which
    will result in a DiscoveryRequest for corresponding client
    proxies. Service field updates that should result in an
    envoy config change are also taken care of by corresponding
    endpoint updates because endpoint name/port/protocol are
    derived from the service object.
    
    The only scenario where a proxy should be updated when a pod
    is updated is when the metrics configuration for the proxy
    is turned on/off via the metrics label. In this case, this
    change ensures only the specific proxy is updated.
    
    Part of #4256
    
    Signed-off-by: Shashank Ram <shashr2204@gmail.com>

