[33mcommit 4deb9d8defafb29f0f18bd33d4b4f3267cb03792[m
Merge: 75562ac3 c055b1de
Author: Jon Huhn <nojnhuh@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon Oct 11 10:31:26 2021 -0500

    Merge pull request #4234 from nojnhuh/mem
    
    fix(ads): properly sync proxy disconnect

[33mcommit c055b1de19d2dbd750f3dd65a0b1faa0b3612e92[m
Author: Jon Huhn <johuhn@microsoft.com>
Date:   Fri Oct 8 16:05:39 2021 -0500

    fix(ads): properly sync proxy disconnect
    
    This change fixes a goroutine leak leading to high memory usage when
    Pods with proxies are being churned. The `StreamAggregatedResources()`
    function launches a new goroutine running `receive()` whenever a new
    proxy connects to osm-controller. Proxies may disconnect in a few
    different scenarios, but from logs the most common case seemed to be
    on `ctx.Done()` from inside `StreamAggregatedResources()`. When that
    condition was hit however, nothing signalled the `receive()` goroutine
    to stop, so those would run forever even after a proxy disconnected.
    
    This change moves listening for `ctx.Done()` to `receive()` and relies
    on `StreamAggregatedResources()` to exit when `receive()` finishes like
    it was doing before.
    
    Related to #4206
    
    Signed-off-by: Jon Huhn <johuhn@microsoft.com>

