[33mcommit d0d5d9721752b07b3e3d0147ebb8c596d3ab1ed3[m
Author: Shashank Ram <21697719+shashankram@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed Oct 6 10:13:09 2021 -0700

    envoy/registry: do not track disconnected proxies (#4216)
    
    Proxies are expected to disconnect when the corresponding
    pods are recycled.
    Since the cluster can go through a lot of churn, keeping
    track of disconnected proxies results in additional
    memory consumption and bookkeeping which is better avoided.
    It is easy enough to know how many times a proxy has
    reconnected to a control plane after a disconnect using
    the osm_proxy_reconnect_count metric.
    
    Signed-off-by: Shashank Ram <shashr2204@gmail.com>

[33mcommit 0309a0fd42d2bba1929234a1c358db5d72c5a324[m
Author: Shashank Ram <21697719+shashankram@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Oct 5 16:21:36 2021 -0700

    messaging: use message broker in control plane (#4212)
    
    This change refactors the control plane to use
    the message broker for internal message passing
    as opposed to using the global pub-sub instance.
    
    It addresses existing issues around deadlocks and
    blocked channels arising from using the pub-sub
    incorrectly, while removing arbitrary sizing of
    buffered channels and timeouts previously encoded
    in the dispatcher component. Previously, the controller
    would hang as it would be blocked from processing
    events when the channels were at capacity.
    
    At a high level, the change does the following:
    
    - Deprecates the global pub-sub in favor of
      using the message broker which internally
      manages dedicated pub-sub instances for different
      messages.
    
    - Fixes deadlocks and blocked channels that arose
      from using the global pub-sub. The 512 channel
      size masked issues until the channel was at
      capacity. Moreover, unsubscriptions of channels
      were not handled correctly.
    
    - Updates the k8s event handler functions to simply
      queue the item into a workqueue for further processing
      instead of directly publishing events.
    
    - Updates code previously relying on the global
      pub-sub to use the message broker.
    
    - Refactors helper goroutines to follow the pattern
      of running unless signalled to stop.
    
    - Reimplements Ticker to simplify ticker start/stop
      mechanism. Previous implementation was unnecessarily
      complex.
    
    - Refactors tests to remove dependency on pub-sub
      when testing functions that access the caches.
    
    - Removes the experimental code for async proxy-service
      mapping which is un-optimal and deadlocks. This needs
      to be re-implemented to address existing limitations.
    
    Resolves #4167
    
    Testing done:
    
    - Tested this change and verified that deadlocks and
      channel blocking issues are addressed.
    
    Signed-off-by: Shashank Ram <shashr2204@gmail.com>

[33mcommit 1caae978f9b60297bb11aeeee0a09bd8e6adc44c[m[33m ([m[1;32mbackportDisableSmiTest[m[33m)[m
